Alitalia &lt;AZPI.MI> pilots started fivedays of industrial action today causing cancellations to dozensof domestic flights and chaos to several internationalservices, Italian airport officials said.    Pilots working for the national airline are striking forfour hours during the busy morning period every day untilSaturday in protest at working conditions. Almost all ofItaly's airports are affected by the action.    Alitalia said it had cancelled 96 domestic flights andwarned of severe disruption to other services. REUTER&#3;